GORDON Brown has said he could return to front-line politics in Scotland to take on Alex Salmond. Brown will fight NHS 'lies' GORDON Brown has said he could return to front-line politics in Scotland to take on Alex Salmond.Mr Brown accused the First Minister of deceiving voters about the future of the NHS and said that if Mr Salmond continues to &quot;peddle lies&quot; about the NHS he would join Johann Lamont to take on the SNP.He said &quot;If he continues to peddle this deception that the Scottish Parliament under his leadership cannot do anything to improve the health service until he has a separate state, then I will want to join Johann Lamont in fighting him in securing the return of a Labour government as quickly as possible.&quot; 